following http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/BAMBOO/Creating+a+Custom+Elastic+Image
assumes the following artifacts to be in webapp/atlassian-bamboo-agent-elastic-assembly-2.4.0.tar.gz
* bamboo-capabilities.properties  in {{components/bamboo-agent-elastic-image-default/src/main/ec2}}
* rc.local in {{components/bamboo-agent-elastic-image-default/src/main/ec2}}

The url decode for the artifact file serve is limited to utf8
{code:title=ArtifactDownloadStrategy}dataPath = URLDecoder.decode(dataPath, "UTF-8");{code}

If the system encoding is different (say Cp1251) then even if the url that links to the artifact is encoded correctly is cannot be decoded correctly.

